    <title>Linkage classes of grade 3 perfect ideals</title>
    <summary>  While every grade 2 perfect ideal in a regular local ring is linked to a
complete intersection ideal, it is known not to be the case for ideals of grade
3. We soften the blow by proving that every grade 3 perfect ideal in a regular
local ring is linked to a complete intersection or a Golod ideal. Our proof is
indebted to a homological classification of Cohen-Macaulay local rings of
codimension 3. That debt is swiftly repaid, as we use linkage to reveal some of
the finer structures of this classification.
</summary>
